                     <interp inst="t18010415-103-person1065" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn. - I am a constable of Kensington, I apprehended the prisoners; I found two silver tea-spoons upon Byfield, (Producing them).(The spoons were identified by Mrs. Bradley.)</p>
               <p>Byfield did not say any thing in his defence.</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="180104150068"></xptr>Wilson's defence. I know nothing at all of the transaction. Byfield, <rs id="t18010415-103-verdict582" type="verdictDescription">
